title: My device connected to E5373s-155’s wireless network, but cannot open Web UI
answer:
A: 

 1. Double ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=39168) to check your wireless network connection on windows start bar. Make sure your device is connected with your E5373s-155 not other Wi-Fi device. 

 2. Open Web Browser from your device (ex. Microsoft Internet Explorer). Go *<u>http://192.168.8.1</u>* to open E5373s-155’s Web UI.![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=39169) 

 3. If Web Browser failed to bring you to Web UI, click “Tool” from Browser then select “Internet Options”.![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=39170) 

 Select “Connections” tab, then click “LAN settings”. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=39172) 

 For the “Local Area Network (LAN) Settings” pop-up, uncheck the top three check-boxes. Then click “OK” to apply changes. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=39173) 

 Refresh the Web Browser to show E5373s-155 management console page.
